# Supabase

Handle Supabase work yourself — do not ask the user to run SQL in the dashboard or deploy functions manually.

## CLI

- Run from repo root: `npx supabase <command>`
- Project ref: `goacefzxrwwzxfwkioit` (from `mobile/.env`)
- Auth: use `SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN` if set; otherwise run `npx supabase login` (needs user approval once) or link with `npx supabase link --project-ref goacefzxrwwzxfwkioit`

## Migrations

- SQL lives in `supabase/migrations/`
- After adding or changing migrations, apply them: `npx supabase db push`
- Do not tell the user to paste migration SQL unless CLI auth is blocked and you cannot proceed

## Edge functions

- Source: `supabase/functions/`
- Deploy: `npx supabase functions deploy <name> --project-ref goacefzxrwwzxfwkioit`

## App integration

- Public keys: `mobile/.env` (`EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`, `EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`)
- Client: `mobile/src/lib/supabase.ts`
- User data table + RLS: `supabase/migrations/001_user_data.sql`
